  "prompt": "## OAuth 2 Scope Handling: `add_token` Scope Validation\n\nIn OAuth 2 clients, before attaching a bearer token to a request, the client must validate that the requested scope is a subset of the token's granted scope. If the requested scope contains any scope string not present in the granted scope, the request should be rejected.\n\n### Your Task\n\nImplement the following function:\n\n```python\ndef validate_token_scope(token_scope: str, requested_scope: str) -> bool:\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `token_scope`: A space-separated string of scope values that were granted by the authorization server (e.g. `\"read write profile\"`).\n- `requested_scope`: A space-separated string of scope values that the client is requesting to use for this particular call (e.g. `\"read write\"`).\n\n**Return value:**\n- Return `True` if every scope in `requested_scope` is present in `token_scope`.\n- Return `False` if any scope in `requested_scope` is **not** present in `token_scope`.\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- An empty `requested_scope` string (or a string of only whitespace) is always valid — return `True`.\n- An empty `token_scope` string (or whitespace-only) with a non-empty `requested_scope` is always invalid — return `False`.\n- Scope comparison is **case-sensitive**: `\"Read\"` ≠ `\"read\"`.\n- Duplicate scope values in either parameter should not affect the result (treat scope sets, not multisets).\n- Extra whitespace between scope tokens should be tolerated (e.g. `\"read  write\"` is the same as `\"read write\"`).\n\n### Signature\n\n```python\ndef validate_token_scope(token_scope: str, requested_scope: str) -> bool:\n    ...\n```\n\nYou may only use the Python standard library.",
